main event: A civilian witness observed a bright, round, metallic object hovering about 100 feet off the ground and 100 feet from him on September 17, 1966 around 8:30 PM.
interesting points: The object remained stationary for about 2-3 minutes before starting to move rapidly in a zigzag fashion, first up, then down, then sideways.
The witness went to get his camera but when he returned the object had disappeared.
The witness has seen additional UFOs in the past and describes the object as consistent with an aircraft or aircraft lighting.
Another witness reported seeing a bright light in the sky on August 27, 1966 that appeared to be a solid object with a door opening on the side.
The witness is convinced the object was not a bird, plane, or any conventional type of aircraft as it was completely silent and moved with no visible means of propulsion.
